{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"A Blog","author":"Scott Williams"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"64b59def-4d2c-5d4b-96bc-3a695eb2b4e0","excerpt":"GarageBand is a decent amateur audio editor and is also free. I use it to edit  my podcast , which has worked out ok.  Dealing with audio buzzing or humming can…","html":"<p>GarageBand is a decent amateur audio editor and is also free. I use it to edit <a href=\"http://fronttoback.co\">my podcast</a>, which has worked out ok. </p>\n<p>Dealing with audio buzzing or humming can be a problem. Sometimes this can be <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spill_%28audio%29\">headphone bleed</a>, or ambient noise, or anything. A <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Noise_gate\">noise gate</a> can fix that up pretty well if it isn’t too loud<sup id=\"fnref:1\"><a href=\"#fn:1\" rel=\"footnote\">1</a></sup>. What a noise gate does is analyze your audio and mutes any sound that is below a certain volume. GarageBand has this built-in but it is a little hard to find. It’s interface has changed over different versions, so googling around for it often yields out of date information. Here is where it is in version <strong>10</strong>.</p>\n<p>First click this knobby button. </p>\n<figure class=\"center\">\n    \n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 53.78787878787878%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\">\n      <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"knobby button\" title=\"\" src=\"/static/615fae30161d228d8799912196a4aa35/fb8a0/knob.png\" srcset=\"/static/615fae30161d228d8799912196a4aa35/1a291/knob.png 148w,\n/static/615fae30161d228d8799912196a4aa35/2bc4a/knob.png 295w,\n/static/615fae30161d228d8799912196a4aa35/fb8a0/knob.png 590w,\n/static/615fae30161d228d8799912196a4aa35/526de/knob.png 885w,\n/static/615fae30161d228d8799912196a4aa35/fa2eb/knob.png 1180w,\n/static/615fae30161d228d8799912196a4aa35/7f419/knob.png 1584w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n</figure>\n<p>This’ll bring up a panel at the bottom with some additional controls. Click the information “i” button, turn off “Master”, and click “Controls” from the segmented control.</p>\n<figure class=\"center\">\n    \n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 9.021601016518424%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAACCAYAAABYBvyLAAAACXBIWXMAABYlAAAWJQFJUiTwAAAAfklEQVQI11XHPQ8BMQCA4fsfImnlEitNOW2lrVSOGk5EJGwGi4npjBb/+/WxyA3P8BR1bsirmhgjy5Tw3nc457DW/n1vDHZW/VTTCS5mwvqIDwuK4OYkZxmNFVprlFIdZVkihEBK+TFA9HsM7QZ1aNH7O+bUsrs8ud5ebM8P3lFnRKdcyeKNAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\">\n      <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"controls\" title=\"\" src=\"/static/9a4e2effebd58035137331d5a7c65c1d/fb8a0/controls.png\" srcset=\"/static/9a4e2effebd58035137331d5a7c65c1d/1a291/controls.png 148w,\n/static/9a4e2effebd58035137331d5a7c65c1d/2bc4a/controls.png 295w,\n/static/9a4e2effebd58035137331d5a7c65c1d/fb8a0/controls.png 590w,\n/static/9a4e2effebd58035137331d5a7c65c1d/526de/controls.png 885w,\n/static/9a4e2effebd58035137331d5a7c65c1d/fa2eb/controls.png 1180w,\n/static/9a4e2effebd58035137331d5a7c65c1d/08f6a/controls.png 1770w,\n/static/9a4e2effebd58035137331d5a7c65c1d/97b01/controls.png 3148w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n</figure>\n<p>Finally, you’ll have a checkbox labeled “Noise Gate” in that info side panel. Check it to turn it on, and use the slider to adjust how big of a gate you want.</p>\n<figure class=\"center\">\n    \n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 59.480519480519476%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\">\n      <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"noise gate\" title=\"\" src=\"/static/3da8884d889432301ba1307f351a4aff/fb8a0/noise-gate.png\" srcset=\"/static/3da8884d889432301ba1307f351a4aff/1a291/noise-gate.png 148w,\n/static/3da8884d889432301ba1307f351a4aff/2bc4a/noise-gate.png 295w,\n/static/3da8884d889432301ba1307f351a4aff/fb8a0/noise-gate.png 590w,\n/static/3da8884d889432301ba1307f351a4aff/526de/noise-gate.png 885w,\n/static/3da8884d889432301ba1307f351a4aff/fa2eb/noise-gate.png 1180w,\n/static/3da8884d889432301ba1307f351a4aff/d2fec/noise-gate.png 1540w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n</figure>\n<p>This will set the gate on the <em>entire</em> track that is selected up in the main UI. You can have different gates for different tracks, but I don’t think you can different ones on a single track in GarageBand.</p>\n<p>Once I scrape together a little more cash I might go out and get <a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/logic-pro-x/id634148309?mt=12&#x26;uo=4&#x26;at=11lxUn\">Logic Pro</a>. For now though, GarageBand works well enough.</p>\n<div class=\"footnotes\">\n  <ol>\n    <li class=\"footnote\" id=\"fn:1\">\n  <p>Shoutout to <a href=\"https://twitter.com/jmetzendorf\">Jim Metzendorf</a> for helping me out with this.</p>\n</li>\n  </ol>\n</div>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to Add a Noise Gate in GarageBand 10","date":"December 02, 2014"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2014/12/02/how-to-add-a-noise-gate-in-garageband-10/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2014/12/01/my-new-podcast/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"My New Podcast"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2014/12/02/lets-talk-photo-licensing/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Let's Talk Photo Licensing"}}}}